-- Norilsk Nickel, Gazprom, Rosneft May Move: Russian Stock Market Preview
-- Stephen Bierman
-- 2010-07-09T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/norilsk-nickel-gazprom-rosneft-may-move-russian-stock-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  
 Russia’s ruble-based Micex Index fell 0.5 percent yesterday
to 1,320.64 in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS rose 0.3
percent to 1,356.09.  
 OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX): Russia’s largest miner
said 2009 dividend payments may be delayed as former Chairman
 Alexander Voloshin  has refused to sign off on a June 28 board
election. Norilsk shares rose 0.2 percent to 4,776.34 rubles in
Moscow.  
 OAO Gazprom  (GAZP RX): Russia’s gas export monopoly said it
had agreed with Japan to start an investment study into building
a liquefied natural gas plant in Vladivostok on Russia’s Pacific
Coast. Russia’s largest company fell 0.6 percent to 151.98
rubles.  
 OAO Rosneft  (ROSN RX): Crude oil rose to a one-week high as
U.S. jobless claims fell and inventories dropped. Russia’s
largest oil producer fell 1.1 percent to 188.71 rubles. Russia’s
second-largest oil producer  OAO Lukoil  fell 0.3 percent to
1,596.50 rubles in Moscow.  
